(38, 1, '2023-02-03 18:14:49', '2023-02-03 18:14:49', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Problem statement: I have a sticky header and when I am clicking the table on the content link it\'s scrolled to the top and hidden behind the sticky header.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Solution</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>use the scroll-margin-top CSS property on the section to scroll to the top with the given margin</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>scroll-margin-top: 20px;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The table of content contains headings that need to be set on the scroll-margin-top equal to the height of the header</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.blog h1,\r\n.blog h2,\r\n.blog h3,\r\n.blog h4,\r\n.blog h5 {\r\n  scroll-margin-top: 80px;\r\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'How to fix hash navigation with a sticky header', 'How to fix hash navigation with a sticky header. solved table of content hash navigation section hidden behind header', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-fix-hash-navigation-with-a-sticky-header', '', '', '2023-02-07 19:56:35', '2023-02-07 19:56:35', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=38', 0, 'post', '', 0),
