(64, 1, '2023-02-06 15:23:42', '2023-02-06 15:23:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By default next js scroll at the top when navigating to another page or link, there is also a way by which you can stop scrolling when navigating to another page or URL.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Solution</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Check whether your layout is <strong>not</strong> set to <strong><code>overflow:auto</code></strong> or <strong><code>max-height : 100vh</code></strong> something due to which it\'s not scrolling to the top because the content is just set to max height 100vh.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"textColor\":\"vivid-green-cyan\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-vivid-green-cyan-color has-text-color\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/BXzZdQacTfcHjyyRJGDBNx\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/BXzZdQacTfcHjyyRJGDBNx\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>join WhatsApp group</strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Next js Link component</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>there are the following props for the link component in next js which can be used</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>href</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Href is the path of the page or which you want to navigate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>scroll</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is used to set whether the page should be scrolled at the top or not after navigating</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>shallow</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shallow is used to update the path of the current page without rerunning getStaticProps, getServerSideProps, or getInitialProps. its default value is false.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>prefetch</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add a prefetch prop if you want to prefetch that page in the background. The link is by default prefetched.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Alternate methods to solve scrolling problem</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also use the following ways to solve this scrolling problem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>scroll top after on routeChangeComplete</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use <a href=\"https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next/router\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next/router\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">router </a>events to scroll the content to the top of the navigation complete.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import \"@/styles/globals.css\";\r\n\rimport { useRouter } from \'next/router\'\nexport default function App({ Component, pageProps }) {\n\r  const router=useRouter()\n  useEffect(()=>{\n   Router.events.on(\"routeChangeComplete\", () => {\r\n    window.scrollTo(0,0)\r\n    });\n   },&#91;])\n  return &lt;Component {...pageProps} />;\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'How to fix, Next.js link doesn\'t render with the page scrolled at the top', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-fix-next-js-link-doesnt-render-with-the-page-scrolled-at-the-top', '', '', '2023-02-06 15:27:40', '2023-02-06 15:27:40', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=64', 0, 'post', '', 0),
