efetch</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add a prefetch prop if you want to prefetch that page in the background. The link is by default prefetched.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Alternate methods to solve scrolling problem</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also use the following ways to solve this scrolling problem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>scroll top after on routeChangeComplete</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Use <a href=\"https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next/router\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://nextjs.org/docs/api-reference/next/router\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">router </a>events to scroll the content to the top of the navigation complete.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import \"@/styles/globals.css\";\r\n\rimport { useRouter } from \'next/router\'\nexport default function App({ Component, pageProps }) {\n\r  const router=useRouter()\n  useEffect(()=>{\n   Router.events.on(\"routeChangeComplete\", () => {\r\n    window.scrollTo(0,0)\r\n    });\n   },&#91;])\n  return &lt;Component {...pageProps} />;\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'How to fix, Next.js link doesn\'t render with the page scrolled at the top', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '64-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-02-06 15:27:40', '2023-02-06 15:27:40', '', 64, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=67', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(68, 1, '2023-02-07 15:57:18', '2023-02-07 15:57:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To update an object key in the state select the key and assign its value to that state</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>for example,</strong> if we have an object of books and we want to update the physics book name then we can do it in the following way</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":70,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/usetsate-with-object-array.png\" alt=\"react hooks usestsate with object and array\" class=\"wp-image-70\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">react hooks usestsate with object and array</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preserve previous value</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>use the spread operator(...) to preserve the previous value and only update the particular key so that no other keys override</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Update the object key</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>{...prev, key</strong>: <strong>value</strong>} in object literal preserve the object\'s previous value and update the desired key </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import { useState } from \"react\";\n\nconst demo = () =&gt; {\n  const &#91;books, setBooks] = useState({\n    physics: \"\",\n    chemistry: \"\",\n    math: \"\",\n  });\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;\n      &lt;p&gt;List of books&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;form&gt;\n        &lt;input\n          type=\"subject\"\n          name=\"book\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setBooks((prev) =&gt; ({\n              ...prev,\n              physics: e.target.value,\n            }))\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;button&gt;Update book&lt;/button&gt;\n      &lt;/form&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  );\n};\n\nexport default demo;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>how to update array object key in useState</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the same, we can also update the array but in the array, we will have to map to preserve other items of the array and use a filter to update that particular item of the array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import { useState } from \"react\";\n\nconst demo = () =&gt; {\n  const &#91;faq, setFaq] = useState(&#91;\n    {\n      que: \"\",\n      ans: \"\",\n    },\n  ]);\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;\n      &lt;p&gt;List of books&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;form&gt;\n        &lt;input\n          type=\"subject\"\n          name=\"que\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setFaq((prev) =&gt;\n              prev.map((el, index) =&gt; {\n                if (index == i) {\n                  return {\n                    ...el,\n                    que: e.target.value,\n                  };\n                }\n              })\n            )\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;textarea\n          name=\"ans\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setFaq((prev) =&gt;\n              prev.map((el, index) =&gt; {\n                if (index == i) {\n                  return {\n                    ...el,\n                    ans: e.target.value,\n                  };\n                }\n              })\n            )\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;button&gt;Update book&lt;/button&gt;\n      &lt;/form&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  );\n};\n\nexport default demo;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to update the nested objects in useState</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>sometimes we are required to use nested objects in useState, in that case, it becomes difficult to update a key of an object in the useState set method. So let\'s see how to update the nested object in usetstate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>  const &#91;data, setdata] = useState({\n    width: \"160\",\n    text: \"button\",\n    padding: \"17\",\n    border: {\n      width: \"1\",\n      type: \"solid\",\n      color: \"red\",\n      radius: \"20\",\n    },\n\n    background: {\n      isSolid: true,\n      color: \"red\",\n      gradient: { bg1: \"red\", bg2: \"blue\", angle: \"120\" },\n    },\n    textShadow: {\n      x: \"1\",\n      y: \"-1\",\n      blur: \"1\",\n      color: \"\",\n    },\n  });\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>above useState object is nested in 3 levels.<br>here I am updating the blur key of textshadow object</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;input type=\"range\"\n   onChange={(e) =&gt;setdata((prev) =&gt; ({\n                        ...prev,\n                        textShadow: {\n                          ...prev.textShadow,\n                          blur: e.target.value,\n                        },\n                      }))\n                    }\n/&gt;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'how to set object key in useState, react state hook with the object and array', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-set-object-key-in-usestate-react-state-hook-with-the-object-and-array', '', '', '2023-02-10 19:23:04', '2023-02-10 19:23:04', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=68', 0, 'post', '', 0),
