(90, 1, '2023-02-08 16:53:20', '2023-02-08 16:53:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Highlight js is a library to highlight the syntax of programming languages like HTML, CSS js, java,c, c++, etc. There is no proper documentation for react to implement highlight js.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>npm i highlight.js</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to use highlight js in react component</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After installing the package import highlight js and call in use effect hook as it will be applied on the code after the dom content is loaded. You can also override the CSS according to your own.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import \"highlight.js/styles/github.css\";\r\nimport hljs from \"highlight.js\";\r\nimport { useEffect } from \"react\";\r\nconst demo = () => {\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    hljs.highlightAll();\r\n  }, &#91;]);\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    &lt;>\r\n      &lt;code>\r\n        &lt;pre>\r\n          &lt;div class=\"main\">\r\n            &lt;div class=\"post\">\r\n              &lt;button class=\"readmore\">read more&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more1&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more2&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more3&lt;/button>\r\n            &lt;/div>\r\n          &lt;/div>\r\n        &lt;/pre>\r\n      &lt;/code>\r\n    &lt;/>\r\n  );\r\n};\r\n\r\nexport default demo;\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>by default, highlight js selects <strong>&lt;code> </strong>tag to highlight but you can configure your own element also to highlight code if you are placing the code in any other tag instead of the<strong> code </strong>tag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":89,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/hightlight-js-in-react-js-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-89\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We strongly recommend <code>&lt;pre>&lt;code></code> wrapping for code blocks. It\'s quite semantic and \"just works\" out of the box with zero fiddling</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><cite>highlight js</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to ignore code block to highlight</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use nohighlight class to ignore the code block to highlight.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;pre>&lt;code class=\"nohighlight\">...&lt;/code>&lt;/pre></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Highlighting code with specific language</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To highlight code with a specific language, use <code>highlight</code> in the following way</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>html = hljs.highlight(\'&lt;h1>Hello World!&lt;/h1>\', {language: \'xml\'}).value</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Highlighting code after dom content load</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To initiate <a href=\"https://highlightjs.org/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://highlightjs.org/\">highlight.js</a> after dom content loads call it after the dom content loaded event</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>document.addEventListener(\'DOMContentLoaded\', (event) => {\r\n  document.querySelectorAll(\'pre code\').forEach((el) => {\r\n    hljs.highlightElement(el);\r\n  });\r\n});</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To highlight custom code blocks manually:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// first, find all the div.code blocks\r\ndocument.querySelectorAll(\'div.code\').forEach(el => {\r\n  // then highlight each\r\n  hljs.highlightElement(el);\r\n});</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/\">check more demos here</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to add highlight.js in react', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '87-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-02-08 16:53:20', '2023-02-08 16:53:20', '', 87, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=90', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2023-02-10 19:21:32', '2023-02-10 19:21:32', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To update an object key in the state select the key and assign its value to that state</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>for example,</strong> if we have an object of books and we want to update the physics book name then we can do it in the following way</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":70,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/usetsate-with-object-array.png\" alt=\"react hooks usestsate with object and array\" class=\"wp-image-70\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">react hooks usestsate with object and array</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Preserve previous value</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>use the spread operator(...) to preserve the previous value and only update the particular key so that no other keys override</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Update the object key</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>{...prev, key</strong>: <strong>value</strong>} in object literal preserve the object\'s previous value and update the desired key </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import { useState } from \"react\";\n\nconst demo = () =&gt; {\n  const &#91;books, setBooks] = useState({\n    physics: \"\",\n    chemistry: \"\",\n    math: \"\",\n  });\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;\n      &lt;p&gt;List of books&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;form&gt;\n        &lt;input\n          type=\"subject\"\n          name=\"book\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setBooks((prev) =&gt; ({\n              ...prev,\n              physics: e.target.value,\n            }))\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;button&gt;Update book&lt;/button&gt;\n      &lt;/form&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  );\n};\n\nexport default demo;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>how to update array object key in useState</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the same, we can also update the array but in the array, we will have to map to preserve other items of the array and use a filter to update that particular item of the array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import { useState } from \"react\";\n\nconst demo = () =&gt; {\n  const &#91;faq, setFaq] = useState(&#91;\n    {\n      que: \"\",\n      ans: \"\",\n    },\n  ]);\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;\n      &lt;p&gt;List of books&lt;/p&gt;\n      &lt;form&gt;\n        &lt;input\n          type=\"subject\"\n          name=\"que\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setFaq((prev) =&gt;\n              prev.map((el, index) =&gt; {\n                if (index == i) {\n                  return {\n                    ...el,\n                    que: e.target.value,\n                  };\n                }\n              })\n            )\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;textarea\n          name=\"ans\"\n          onClick={(e) =&gt;\n            setFaq((prev) =&gt;\n              prev.map((el, index) =&gt; {\n                if (index == i) {\n                  return {\n                    ...el,\n                    ans: e.target.value,\n                  };\n                }\n              })\n            )\n          }\n        /&gt;\n        &lt;button&gt;Update book&lt;/button&gt;\n      &lt;/form&gt;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n  );\n};\n\nexport default demo;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to update the nested objects in useState</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>sometimes we are required to use nested objects in useState, in that case, it becomes difficult to update a key of an object in the useState set method. So let\'s see how to update the nested object in usetstate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>  const &#91;data, setdata] = useState({\r\n    link: {\r\n      url: \"\",\r\n      isLink: false,\r\n    },\r\n    width: \"160\",\r\n    text: \"button\",\r\n    padding: \"17\",\r\n    border: {\r\n      width: \"1\",\r\n      type: \"solid\",\r\n      color: \"red\",\r\n      radius: \"20\",\r\n    },\r\n    boxShadow: {\r\n      x: \"0\",\r\n      y: \"2\",\r\n      spread: \"3\",\r\n      blur: \"5\",\r\n      color: \"rgba(0,0,0,0.4)\",\r\n    },\r\n    color: \"green\",\r\n    font: {\r\n      size: \"20\",\r\n      color: \"#fff\",\r\n      bold: \"\",\r\n    },\r\n\r\n    background: {\r\n      isSolid: true,\r\n      color: \"red\",\r\n      gradient: { bg1: \"red\", bg2: \"blue\", angle: \"120\" },\r\n    },\r\n    textShadow: {\r\n      x: \"1\",\r\n      y: \"-1\",\r\n      blur: \"1\",\r\n      color: \"\",\r\n    },\r\n  });\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>above useState object is nested in 3 levels.<br>here I am updating blur key of textshadow object</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;input type=\"range\"\n   onChange={(e) =>setdata((prev) => ({\n                        ...prev,\n                        textShadow: {\n                          ...prev.textShadow,\n                          blur: e.target.value,\n                        },\n                      }))\n                    }\n/></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->', 'how to set object key in useState, react state hook with the object and array', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-02-10 19:21:32', '2023-02-10 19:21:32', '', 68, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=94', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
