(101, 1, '2023-02-14 18:33:51', '2023-02-14 18:33:51', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are going to use the npm package to convert json to csv in react. There are several npm packages for JSON to CSV conversion. Here is the list of npm  packages</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/json-2-csv\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/json-2-csv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">json-2-csv</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/papaparse\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/papaparse\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Papaparse</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-csv\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-csv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">react-csv</a></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lets now see, how to convert json to csv with json-2-csv npm</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>npm i json-2-csv</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Methods available to convert json to csv in json-2-csv</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are two methods available in json-2-csv to convert json to csv synchronous and asynchronous method. It needs three paramater <strong>array of JSON, a callback function and option</strong> for config</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>json2csv(array, (err, csv) =&gt; { ... }, options)</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>json2csvAsync</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>for the asynchronous method, We can use json2csvAsync with async await.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>\nimport { json2csvAsync } from \"json-2-csv\";\nconst Page = () =&gt; {\n      const toCSV = async (myjson) =&gt; {\n        const options = {\n          delimiter: {\n            wrap: \'\"\', // Double Quote (\") character\n            field: \",\",\n            eol: \"\\n\"\n          },\n          //   prependHeader: true,\n          sortHeader: false,\n        };\n        try {\n          const csv = await json2csvAsync(JSON.parse(myjson), {\n            ...options,\n            keys: null,\n          });\n        } catch (err) {\n    \n        }\n      };\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;Page&lt;/div&gt;\n  )\n}\n\nexport default Page</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>json2csv</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>for the asynchronous method, we will have to pass a callback function</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import { json2csv} from \"json-2-csv\";\nconst Page = () =&gt; {\nlet documents = &#91;\n    {\n        Make: \'Nissan\',\n        Model: \'Murano\',\n        Year: \'2013\',\n        Specifications: {\n            Mileage: \'7106\',\n            Trim: \'S AWD\'\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        Make: \'BMW\',\n        Model: \'X5\',\n        Year: \'2014\',\n        Specifications: {\n            Mileage: \'3287\',\n            Trim: \'M\'\n        }\n    }\n];\nlet json2csvCallback = function (err, csv) {\n    if (err) throw err;\n    console.log(csv);\n};\n\njson2csv(documents, json2csvCallback);\n\n  return (\n    &lt;div&gt;Page&lt;/div&gt;\n  )\n}\n\nexport default Page</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are npm packages we can use to convert <a style=\"text-decoration:none;color:inherit\" href=\"https://www.jsonviewer.guru/json-to-csv\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.jsonviewer.guru/json-to-csv\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">json to csv</a> in javascript, react or next js</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to convert JSON to CSV in react js', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-convert-json-to-csv-in-react-js', '', '', '2023-02-14 18:39:24', '2023-02-14 18:39:24', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=101', 0, 'post', '', 0),
