rson.city = \"New York\";\r\nconsole.log(person); // Output: { name: \"Jane\", age: 30, city: \"New York\" }\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this example, we assigned the value <code>\"New York\"</code> to the non-existent <code>city</code> key of the <code>person</code> object, effectively creating a new key with the specified value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In summary, you can update the value of an existing key in a JavaScript object by simply assigning a new value to that key, or by using the <code>[]</code> notation. If the key doesn\'t exist, JavaScript will create a new key with the specified value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to update key with new value in javascript', 'How to update key with new value in javascript,In JavaScript, you can update the value of an existing key in an object by simply assigning a new value to that key.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '164-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-02-23 16:24:52', '2023-02-23 16:24:52', '', 164, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=165', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(166, 1, '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the <code>setDate()</code> method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// create a new date object\r\nvar date = new Date();\r\n\r\n// add 7 days to the date\r\ndate.setDate(date.getDate() + 7);\r\n\r\n// output the new date as a string\r\nconsole.log(date.toDateString());\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this example, we create a new <code>Date</code> object and then use the <code>setDate()</code> method to add 7 days to the current day of the month. We use the <code>getDate()</code> method to get the current day of the month and add 7 to it, and then pass that value to the <code>setDate()</code> method. Finally, we output the new date as a string using the <code>toDateString()</code> method.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can replace <code>7</code> it with any number of days you want to add to the date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to add days to date in javascript', 'To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the setDate() method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'javascript-add-days-to-date', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=166', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(167, 1, '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the <code>setDate()</code> method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// create a new date object\r\nvar date = new Date();\r\n\r\n// add 7 days to the date\r\ndate.setDate(date.getDate() + 7);\r\n\r\n// output the new date as a string\r\nconsole.log(date.toDateString());\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this example, we create a new <code>Date</code> object and then use the <code>setDate()</code> method to add 7 days to the current day of the month. We use the <code>getDate()</code> method to get the current day of the month and add 7 to it, and then pass that value to the <code>setDate()</code> method. Finally, we output the new date as a string using the <code>toDateString()</code> method.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can replace <code>7</code> it with any number of days you want to add to the date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'javascript add days to date', 'To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the setDate() method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '2023-02-23 16:31:31', '', 166, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=167', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(168, 1, '2023-02-24 18:09:00', '2023-02-24 18:09:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To style a Squarespace newsletter button using CSS, you can follow these steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>First, locate the newsletter block on your Squarespace website and click on the Edit button.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>Next, click on the Design tab and scroll down to the Custom CSS field.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>In the Custom CSS field, you can add the following CSS code to style your newsletter button:</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.newsletter-form-button {\r\n  background-color: #FFA500; /* Change the color to your desired hex code */\r\n  color: #FFFFFF; /* Change the text color to your desired color */\r\n  border: none; /* Remove the border */\r\n  padding: 10px 20px; /* Change the padding to your desired size */\r\n  border-radius: 5px; /* Add rounded corners to the button */\r\n  font-size: 16px; /* Change the font size to your desired size */\r\n  font-weight: bold; /* Make the text bold */\r\n  text-transform: uppercase; /* Change the text to uppercase */\r\n  cursor: pointer; /* Add a pointer cursor on hover */\r\n}\r\n\r\n.newsletter-form-button:hover {\r\n  background-color: #FFC107; /* Change the hover color to your desired hex code */\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you\'ve added the CSS code, click Save to apply the changes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Note: The CSS code above is just an example, you can modify the values to suit your design preferences.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to modify Squarespace newsletter button css ?', 'Squarespace newsletter button css,To style a Squarespace newsletter button using CSS, you can follow these steps: ', 'publi