(208, 1, '2023-03-25 11:46:20', '2023-03-25 11:46:20', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this article we will see <strong>CSS selectors in Hindi </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CSS चयनकर्ता (<a href=\"/blog/css-advanced-selectors\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"/blog/css-advanced-selectors\">Selectors</a>) वे तरीके होते हैं जो आपको वेबपेज के विभिन्न तत्वों के साथ जोड़ने की अनुमति देते हैं। ये निम्नलिखित होते हैं:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>तत्व चयनकर्ता (Element Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम विभिन्न तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \"p\" चयनकर्ता हमें सभी पैराग्राफ तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>आईडी चयनकर्ता (ID Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम किसी एक विशिष्ट तत्व को चुन सकते हैं। यह एक यूनिक आईडी हो सकता है जो विशिष्ट होता है। उदाहरण के लिए, \"#main\" चयनकर्ता हमें \"main\" आईडी वाले तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>वर्ग चयनकर्ता (Class Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम एक या एक से अधिक तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं जो एक विशिष्ट वर्ग से संबंधित होते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \".red\" चयनकर्ता हमें \"red\" वर्ग से संबंधित सभी तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>संबंध चयनकर्ता (Descendant Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम एक तत</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":5} -->\n<ol start=\"5\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>विशेषता चयनकर्ता (Attribute Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं जो एक विशिष्ट विशेषता को होल्ड करते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \"[href]\" चयनकर्ता हमें \"href\" विशेषता वाले सभी तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>पेशेवर चयनकर्ता (Pseudo Selectors) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं जो विशेष स्थितियों में होते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \":hover\" चयनकर्ता हमें होवर होने पर तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>चयनकर्ता समूह (Selector Combinators) - इन चयनकर्ताओं के माध्यम से हम एक से अधिक चयनकर्ताओं को जोड़ सकते हैं जिससे हम विशिष्ट तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \"div p\" चयनकर्ता हमें \"div\" तत्व के अंदर \"p\" तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":8} -->\n<ol start=\"8\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>संयोजन चयनकर्ता (Combinators) - इन चयनकर्ताओं के माध्यम से हम तत्वों को चुनने के लिए अन्य तत्वों से संयोजन कर सकते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \"+\" चयनकर्ता हमें उस तत्व को चुनने में मदद करता है जो दूसरे तत्व से बाईं ओर स्थित होता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>शुरुआती चयनकर्ता (First Child, Last Child) - इन चयनकर्ताओं के माध्यम से हम एक तत्व के पहले या आखिरी बच्चे को चुन सकते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \":first-child\" चयनकर्ता हमें पहले बच्चे को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>नकारात्मक चयनकर्ता (Negation) - इस चयनकर्ता के माध्यम से हम उन तत्वों को चुन सकते हैं जो दिए गए चयनकर्ता के साथ संबंधित नहीं होते हैं। उदाहरण के लिए, \":not(p)\" चयनकर्ता हमें \"p\" तत्व से अलग तत्वों को चुनने में मदद करता है।</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ये थे कुछ अन्य मुख्य CSS चयनकर्ता हिंदी में। इन चयनकर्ताओं का उपयोग करके, हम अपनी वेबसाइट के लिए स्टाइल और लेआउट को निर्धारित कर सकते हैं।</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Top 15 advanced CSS selectors in Hindi ', 'CSS selectors in Hindi ,CSS चयनकर्ता (Selectors) वे तरीके होते हैं जो आपको वेबपेज के विभिन्न तत्वों के साथ जोड़ने की अनुमति देते हैं। ये निम्नलिखित होते हैं', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:46:20', '2023-03-25 11:46:20', '', 176, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=208', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(209, 1, '2023-03-25 11:46:57', '2023-03-25 11:46:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The error message you\'re seeing indicates that your code is trying to import a module called <code>react-dom/client</code> from a file named <code>pure.js</code>, but it cannot find the module.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are a few possible reasons for this error:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>The <code>react-dom</code> the package is not installed in your project. Make sure you have installed it using a package manager like npm or yarn.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>You have an outdated version of <code>react-dom</code>. The <code>client </code>module was removed in React 18, so if you\'re using an older version of <code>react-dom</code>, it may not have the <code>client</code> module. Try upgrading to the latest version of <code>react-dom</code>.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>The path to the <code>react-dom/client</code> the module is incorrect. Double-check the path in your import statement to make sure it is pointing to the correct location.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>There is a typo or other error in your code. Check for any syntax errors or other issues in your code that might be causing the import to fail.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you have resolved the issue, the <code>react-dom/client</code> module should be imported successfully.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to fix this error \"cannot find module \'react-dom/client\' from \'pure.js\'\"', 'cannot find module \'react-dom/client\' from \'pure.js\'', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:46:57', '2023-03-25 11:46:57', '', 170, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=209', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2023-03-25 11:47:15', '2023-03-25 11:47:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To style a Squarespace newsletter button using CSS, you can follow these steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>First, locate the newsletter block on your Squarespace website and click on the Edit button.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>Next, click on the Design tab and scroll down to the Custom CSS field.</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><p>In the Custom CSS field, you can add the following CSS code to style your newsletter button:</p></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.newsletter-form-button {\r\n  background-color: #FFA500; /* Change the color to your desired hex code */\r\n  color: #FFFFFF; /* Change the text color to your desired color */\r\n  border: none; /* Remove the border */\r\n  padding: 10px 20px; /* Change the padding to your desired size */\r\n  border-radius: 5px; /* Add rounded corners to the button */\r\n  font-size: 16px; /* Change the font size to your desired size */\r\n  font-weight: bold; /* Make the text bold */\r\n  text-transform: uppercase; /* Change the text to uppercase */\r\n  cursor: pointer; /* Add a pointer cursor on hover */\r\n}\r\n\r\n.newsletter-form-button:hover {\r\n  background-color: #FFC107; /* Change the hover color to your desired hex code */\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once you\'ve added the CSS code, click Save to apply the changes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Note: The CSS code above is just an example, you can modify the values to suit your design preferences.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to modify Squarespace newsletter button css ?', 'Squarespace newsletter button css,To style a Squarespace newsletter button using CSS, you can follow these steps: ', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:47:15', '2023-03-25 11:47:15', '', 168, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=210', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(211, 1, '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the <code>setDate()</code> method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// create a new date object\r\nvar date = new Date();\r\n\r\n// add 7 days to the date\r\ndate.setDate(date.getDate() + 7);\r\n\r\n// output the new date as a string\r\nconsole.log(date.toDateString());\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this example, we create a new <code>Date</code> object and then use the <code>setDate()</code> method to add 7 days to the current day of the month. We use the <code>getDate()</code> method to get the current day of the month and add 7 to it, and then pass that value to the <code>setDate()</code> method. Finally, we output the new date as a string using the <code>toDateString()</code> method.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can replace <code>7</code> it with any number of days you want to add to the date.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to add days to date in javascript', 'To add days to a JavaScript date object, you can use the setDate() method to modify the day of the month. Here\'s an example:', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '2023-03-25 11:47:39', '', 166, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=211', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2023-03-25 11:47:53', '2023-03-25 11:47:53', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To set transparent background color you can use rgba color</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Ways to set transparent background color in CSS</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>    Using background color to Set Transparent Background Color in CSS<br><code>background-color:transparent</code></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>  Using Opacity Property to Set Transparent Background Color in CSS<br><code>.bg {opacity : 0.2}</code></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<table className=\"max-content my-4\">\n              <tbody>\n                <tr>\n                  <td>background</td>\n                  <td>red</td>\n                </tr>\n                <tr>\n                  <td>background-image</td>\n                  <td>url(``)</td>\n                </tr>\n              </tbody>\n            </table>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Setting a CSS background color to transparent means that the element\'s background will be see-through, allowing the content behind it to be visible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To set a CSS background color to transparent, you can use the rgba() or hsla() color functions, and specify an alpha value (the last value) of 0, which represents fully transparent. Here\'s an example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code> background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0); /* white with 0% opacity*/</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the example above, the background color is set to white, but the alpha value is 0, making it fully transparent. You can replace the color values with any valid color code, such as hex or color name.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can also use the transparent keyword to set the background color to fully transparent, like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>background-color: transparent;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this case, the keyword transparent is used instead of a color value. This will make the element\'s background fully transparent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to make CSS background color transparent', 'CSS background color transparent,how to set transparent background color in css', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '147-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:47:53', '2023-03-25 11:47:53', '', 147, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=212', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2023-03-25 11:48:22', '2023-03-25 11:48:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>css and svg fish animation for the website to portray animation of swimming fish. You can create svg fish animation using css3 keyframe animation to create animation with svg fish.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<iframe height=\"300\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"Swimming fish animation\" src=\"https://codepen.io/monchito/embed/RPEqvo?default-tab=html%2Cresult\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href=\"https://codepen.io/monchito/pen/RPEqvo\">\n  Swimming fish animation</a> by Monchito (<a href=\"https://codepen.io/monchito\">@monchito</a>)\n  on <a href=\"https://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'How to create svg fish animation in css ?', 'css and svg fish animation for the website to portray animation of swimming fish. You can create svg fish animation using css3 keyframe animation to create animation with svg fish.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '120-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:48:22', '2023-03-25 11:48:22', '', 120, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=213', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2023-03-25 11:48:48', '2023-03-25 11:48:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Blast animation CSS, here is the list of codepen for blast animation CSS. Here is the list of CSS animations you can use for your website to add animation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<iframe height=\"400\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"blast animation css codepen\" src=\"https://codepen.io/fluidoil/embed/GRqWMXW?default-tab=html%2Cresult\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href=\"https://codepen.io/fluidoil/pen/GRqWMXW\">\n  fireworks html5 3.0 kb</a> by fluidoil4.@gmail.com (<a href=\"https://codepen.io/fluidoil\">@fluidoil</a>)\n  on <a href=\"https://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>star animation css codepen</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<iframe height=\"370\" style=\"width: 100%;\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"star animation css codepen\" src=\"https://codepen.io/theslladev/embed/gOeZqJr?default-tab=html%2Cresult\" frameborder=\"no\" loading=\"lazy\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\">\n  See the Pen <a href=\"https://codepen.io/theslladev/pen/gOeZqJr\">\n  Explosão de confetes de festa - Desafio 27/30 de 30 dias de CSS(Party Confetti Explosion - 30 Day CSS 27/30 Challenge)</a> by ThesllaDev (<a href=\"https://codepen.io/theslladev\">@theslladev</a>)\n  on <a href=\"https://codepen.io\">CodePen</a>.\n</iframe>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'Sourcecode for blast animation css codepen', 'blast animation css - css animation list for blast animation , star animation, exlotion css animation', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '117-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:48:48', '2023-03-25 11:48:48', '', 117, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=214', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(215, 1, '2023-03-25 11:49:14', '2023-03-25 11:49:14', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Highlight js is a library to highlight the syntax of programming languages like HTML, CSS js, java,c, c++, etc. There is no proper documentation for react to implement highlight js.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>npm i highlight.js</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to use highlight js in react component</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After installing the package import highlight js and call in use effect hook as it will be applied on the code after the dom content is loaded. You can also override the CSS according to your own.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>import \"highlight.js/styles/github.css\";\r\nimport hljs from \"highlight.js\";\r\nimport { useEffect } from \"react\";\r\nconst demo = () => {\r\n  useEffect(() => {\r\n    hljs.highlightAll();\r\n  }, &#91;]);\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    &lt;>\r\n      &lt;code>\r\n        &lt;pre>\r\n          &lt;div class=\"main\">\r\n            &lt;div class=\"post\">\r\n              &lt;button class=\"readmore\">read more&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more1&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more2&lt;/button>\r\n              &lt;button>read more3&lt;/button>\r\n            &lt;/div>\r\n          &lt;/div>\r\n        &lt;/pre>\r\n      &lt;/code>\r\n    &lt;/>\r\n  );\r\n};\r\n\r\nexport default demo;\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>by default, highlight js selects <strong>&lt;code> </strong>tag to highlight but you can configure your own element also to highlight code if you are placing the code in any other tag instead of the<strong> code </strong>tag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":89,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/hightlight-js-in-react-js-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-89\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We strongly recommend <code>&lt;pre>&lt;code></code> wrapping for code blocks. It\'s quite semantic and \"just works\" out of the box with zero fiddling</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><cite>highlight js</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to ignore code block to highlight</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use nohighlight class to ignore the code block to highlight.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;pre>&lt;code class=\"nohighlight\">...&lt;/code>&lt;/pre></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Highlighting code with specific language</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To highlight code with a specific language, use <code>highlight</code> in the following way</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>html = hljs.highlight(\'&lt;h1>Hello World!&lt;/h1>\', {language: \'xml\'}).value</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Highlighting code after dom content load</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To initiate <a href=\"https://highlightjs.org/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://highlightjs.org/\">highlight.js</a> after dom content loads call it after the dom content loaded event</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>document.addEventListener(\'DOMContentLoaded\', (event) => {\r\n  document.querySelectorAll(\'pre code\').forEach((el) => {\r\n    hljs.highlightElement(el);\r\n  });\r\n});</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To highlight custom code blocks manually:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>// first, find all the div.code blocks\r\ndocument.querySelectorAll(\'div.code\').forEach(el => {\r\n  // then highlight each\r\n  hljs.highlightElement(el);\r\n});</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://highlightjs.org/static/demo/\">check more demos here</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How to add highlight.js in react complete solution with sourcecode', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '87-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:49:14', '2023-03-25 11:49:14', '', 87, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=215', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(216, 1, '2023-03-25 11:49:43', '2023-03-25 11:49:43', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>the array is a very important topic in javascript. Almost everywhere it is needed whether we are in frontend or backend with node js, so it becomes necessary to know javascript methods.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>declare an array in js </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>we can declare an array in js by following the methods</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr=&#91;\"1\",\"2\",\"3\"]\n         or\nconst arr=new Array(\"1\",\"2\",\"3\")</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>js length of an array</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const array=&#91;]\nconst length=array.length</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Push item to array in js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const array=&#91;\"apple\",\"grapes\"]\narray.push(\"mango\")</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Find the item in the array</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <code>find()</code> the method returns the value of the first element that passes a test. We pass a filter function to check items that we want to find based on condition.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>find method run for every item in an array</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>it returns undefined if no item is found</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>It does execute for an empty item</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>the find method does not change or manipulate the original array.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const array=&#91;\"mango\",\"apple\",\"grapes\"]\nconst findmango=array.find(el=>el==\"mango\")</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>filter array in js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>filter method in an array is used to filter items from the array. we pass a function to filter items based on the condition it filters out the items in a new array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The filter method does not execute the function on an empty element of the array</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The filter method does not change the original array.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The filter method creates a new array of items returned from the filter function.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const ages = &#91;32, 33, 16, 40];\nconst voters=ages.filter(el=>el>18)</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Js array findall</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>to find all items passed the particular conditions we will have to use the filter method</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr=&#91;10,20,22,50,60]\nconst all_items_above_21 = arr.filter(num=>num>21)</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>findindex method in js array</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The findindex method is used to find an index of an item in the array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>find method executes a function for each element</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>JS empty an array</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There may be multiple ways to empty an array the easiest way is to assign an empty array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr=&#91;\"12\",\"22\",\"17\"]</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Four ways to empty an array in javascript</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Pass empty array</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Set array length to zero</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Delete all elements using splice one by one</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Pop all items of an array.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>let a = &#91;1,2,3];\n\r\n//method 1\na = &#91;];\r\n\n//method 2\na.length = 0;\r\n\n//method 3\na.splice(0,a.length);\n\n//method 4\nwhile(a.length > 0) {\r\n    a.pop();\r\n}\r\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to merge two arrays in js</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>to merge two arrays we can append two arrays using the append method or spread operator.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr1 = &#91;\"Cecilie\", \"Lone\"];\r\nconst arr2 = &#91;1, 2, 3];\n\n\r//method 1\nconst mergedArray = arr1.concat(arr2);\n\n//method 2\nconst mergedArray = &#91;...arr1,...arr2]\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Array concat method</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>concat method joins items of two or more arrays and returns a new array containing the items of all arrays. The Concat method does not change the original array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr1 = &#91;\"mango\", \"apple\"];\r\nconst arr2 = &#91;\"Emil\", \"Tobias\", \"Linus\"];\r\nconst arr3 = &#91;\"ashish\",\"manish\"];\r\nconst children = arr1.concat(arr2, arr3);</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Removing specific elements or item in an array</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are multiple ways to remove array items. we can use the filter or splice method to remove a specific item from an array.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>let value = 3\r\nlet arr = &#91;1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 3]\r\narr = arr.filter(item => item !== value)\r\nconsole.log(arr)\r\narr=&#91;1,2,4,5]</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Removing an element from an array by index. If the index of an item is known then we can use the splice method otherwise we can first find the element index and then we can remove it from the array using the splice method.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>const arr=&#91;1,2,4,5,6,7,8]\nconst index=arr.findindex(el=>el==4)  //find index of item 4\narr.splice(4,1)  //remove 1 item from index 4</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Top important Javascript (js) Array Methods for frontend developers', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '98-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-03-25 11:49:43', '2023-03-25 11:49:43', '', 98, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=216', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
