one number, email, and social media links.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So these were the important steps that how you can start designing and real-world website in HTML and CSS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><a href=\"/blog/top-10-things-to-care-about-while-design-website-for-fast-speed-seo\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"/blog/top-10-things-to-care-about-while-design-website-for-fast-speed-seo\">Also read - Top 10 Things to care about while design website for fast speed &amp; SEO</a></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading --><cite>Read more</cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":257,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/build-responsive-real-world-websites-with-html-and-css-1024x576.png\" alt=\"build responsive real-world websites with html and css\" class=\"wp-image-257\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Steps for advanced website designing for a real-world website </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Plan your website design</strong>: Before you start coding, it\'s essential to plan your website design. You can use tools like Adobe XD or Sketch to create a wireframe or a mockup of your design. Consider the layout, typography, colors, images, and content.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Create the HTML structure</strong>: Once you have a plan, start creating the HTML structure of your website. Use semantic HTML elements to structure your content, such as headings, paragraphs, lists, and divs. Make sure your HTML is well-formed and properly indented.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Apply CSS styling</strong>: Apply CSS styling to your HTML elements to make your website look visually appealing. Use CSS selectors to target specific elements and apply styles, such as font size, color, background, padding, margin, and border. Use external stylesheets to keep your CSS organized and reusable.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Use CSS frameworks</strong>: CSS frameworks like Bootstrap, Foundation, or Bulma can help you build responsive websites quickly. They provide pre-designed components, such as grids, forms, buttons, and navigation bars, that you can customize to fit your design.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Test and optimize</strong>: Test your website on different devices and screen sizes to ensure it looks good and functions properly. Use tools like Google\'s PageSpeed Insights to optimize your website\'s performance, such as page load time, image optimization, and minification of CSS and JavaScript files.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Continuously improve</strong>: Websites are never truly finished. Keep updating your website with new content, features, and improvements based on user feedback and analytics.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remember that building a website requires patience, persistence, and attention to detail. Keep learning and experimenting to improve your skills and build better websites.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Build responsive real-world websites with HTML and CSS ', 'Learn how to build responsive and visually stunning websites with HTML and CSS. This comprehensive guide will teach you how to create real-world websites that adapt to any device', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'build-responsive-real-world-websites-with-html-and-css', '', '', '2023-03-30 17:15:04', '2023-03-30 17:15:04', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=252', 0, 'post', '', 0),
