(265, 1, '2023-04-01 04:59:01', '2023-04-01 04:59:01', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As there is now a standard CSS selector for previous siblings provided by CSS or css3. But we can use some tricks to select the previous siblings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":266,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/previous-sibling-selector-css.png\" alt=\"css selector for previous sibling\" class=\"wp-image-266\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Using has:()</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can target or select the previous siblings by using has:() and immediate siblings\' selectors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>For example,</strong> I want to select 2nd li to color red, for this We can use the logic, to select the child which has an immediate sibling with the class name \".a3\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>    &lt;style>\n        ul li:has(+ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    &lt;/style>\n    &lt;ul>\n        &lt;li class=\"a1\">a1&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a2\">a2&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a3\">a3&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a4\">a4&lt;/li>\n    &lt;/ul></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Document</title>\n    <style>\n        ul li:has(+ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n<h3 class=\"mb-2\">output</h3>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"a1\">a1</li>\n        <li class=\"a2\">a2</li>\n        <li class=\"a3\">a3</li>\n        <li class=\"a4\">a4</li>\n    </ul>\n</body>\n\n</html>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Other examples</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Same as the above example we can use all other css selectors with has:() to select different previous or other sibling elements in HTML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>the following example is to select all previous siblings of the node which has class a3.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code> &lt;style>\n        ul li:has(~ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    &lt;/style>\n    &lt;ul>\n        &lt;li class=\"a1\">a1&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a2\">a2&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a3\">a3&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a4\">a4&lt;/li>\n    &lt;/ul></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n <style>\n        ul.an li:has(~ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    </style>\n    <ul class=\"an\">\n        <li class=\"a1\">a1</li>\n        <li class=\"a2\">a2</li>\n        <li class=\"a3\">a3</li>\n        <li class=\"a4\">a4</li>\n    </ul>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n👉 <a class=\"theme-btn\" href=\"/blog/css-advanced-selectors\">Check other advanced css selectors</a>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'CSS selector for the previous sibling | 99% chance, No one knows this', 'CSS selector for previous sibling. Use the following demo with source code to learn how to select previous sibling in css', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'css-selector-for-the-previous-sibling-99-chance-no-one-knows-this', '', '', '2023-04-01 05:13:32', '2023-04-01 05:13:32', '', 0, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=265', 0, 'post', '', 0),
