 class=\"a4\">a4</li>\n    </ul>\n</body>\n\n</html>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Other examples</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Same as the above example we can use all other css selectors with has:() to select different previous or other sibling elements in HTML.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>the following example is to select all previous siblings of the node which has class a3.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code> &lt;style>\n        ul li:has(~ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    &lt;/style>\n    &lt;ul>\n        &lt;li class=\"a1\">a1&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a2\">a2&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a3\">a3&lt;/li>\n        &lt;li class=\"a4\">a4&lt;/li>\n    &lt;/ul></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n <style>\n        ul li:has(~ .a3) {\n            color: red;\n        }\n    </style>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"a1\">a1</li>\n        <li class=\"a2\">a2</li>\n        <li class=\"a3\">a3</li>\n        <li class=\"a4\">a4</li>\n    </ul>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'CSS selector for the previous sibling | 99% chance, No one knows this', 'CSS selector for previous sibling. Use the following demo with source code to learn how to select previous sibling in css', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '265-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-04-01 04:59:01', '2023-04-01 04:59:01', '', 265, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=267', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
