onment variables in your deployment settings. Different hosting platforms have their own ways of handling environment variables.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Console Logging</strong>: Temporarily add <code>console.log</code> statements to your code to print out the values of environment variables. This can help you diagnose whether the variables are being loaded correctly.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By carefully checking these aspects, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue of your Next.js environment variables being undefined.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Why are Next js environment variables undefined?', 'main reason why your next js environment variable is undefined.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '394-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-08-26 17:16:56', '2023-08-26 17:16:56', '', 394, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=398', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
