     &lt;label for=\"password\">\n                    &lt;input placeholder=\"Password\" id=\"password\" type=\"password\"/>\n                &lt;/label>\n                &lt;label for=\"confirm password\">\n                    &lt;input placeholder=\"confirm password\" id=\"password\"           type=\"password\" />\n                &lt;/label>\n                &lt;button>Sign Up&lt;/button>\n            &lt;/form>\n        &lt;/div>\n    &lt;/body>\n&lt;/html>\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the code above for the HTML form, we have created a registration form which has the following fields:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Email</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>password</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>confirm password</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add more fields according to your need like first name, last name, mobile number, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each input element has a unique <code>id</code> and <code>name</code> attribute, which is essential for JavaScript and server-side processing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now add CSS  in style.css and link it to the HTML file</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>style.css\n\n       /* body{display: flex;align-items: center;min-height: 96vh;} */\r\n            .form {\r\n                display: flex;\r\n                height: 400px;\r\n                width: 700px;\r\n                border-radius: 8px;\r\n                box-shadow: 0 0 8px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\r\n                font-family: sans-serif;\r\n                overflow: hidden;\r\n                margin: 10px auto;\r\n            }\r\n            .form input {\r\n                padding: 10px;\r\n                color: #555;\r\n                border: 2px solid #ddd;\r\n                outline: none;\r\n                font-size: 16px;\r\n                width: 100%;\r\n            }\r\n           .form input:-webkit-autofill {\r\n                -webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 0 1000px #fff inset !important;\r\n            }\r\n            .form input:focus {\r\n                border-color: blue;\r\n            }\r\n            .form img {\r\n                width: 50%;\r\n                height: 100%;\r\n                object-fit: cover;\r\n            }\r\n            .form button {\r\n                padding: 10px 20px;\r\n                font-size: 16px;\r\n                background: blue;\r\n                color: #fff;\r\n                border: none;\r\n                border-radius: 4px;\r\n                width: 100%;\r\n            }\r\n            .form label {\r\n                position: relative;\r\n                margin-bottom: 17px;\r\n            }\r\n            .form label:has(input:focus, input:not(:placeholder-shown)):before {\r\n                top: -22%;\r\n                background: #fff;\r\n                z-index: 1;\r\n                padding: 0 5px;\r\n                transform: none;\r\n                color: #888;\r\n            }\r\n            .form label:has(input:focus)::before {\r\n                color: blue;\r\n            }\r\n            .form input::placeholder {\r\n                opacity: 0;\r\n            }\r\n            .form label::before {\r\n                color: #ccc;\r\n                content: attr(for);\r\n                position: absolute;\r\n                top: 50%;\r\n                transform: translateY(-50%);\r\n                left: 10px;\r\n                pointer-events: none;\r\n                transition: all 0.3s;\r\n            }\r\n            .form h2 {\r\n                margin-top: 0;\r\n            }\r\n            .form form {\r\n                padding: 2rem;\r\n                display: flex;\r\n                flex-direction: column;\