r\n            }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to use this registration form html &amp; css </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use this registration form HTML &amp; CSS either by copying and pasting it into your website or can downloading the file directly and adding it to your website folder. if you are facing any problems in adding this <a href=\"https://codepen.io/tag/registration%20form\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://codepen.io/tag/registration%20form\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">code</a> to your website you can contact me over WhatsApp.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Registration form HTML CSS source code</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now let\'s see how to create a registration form with <a href=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/category/html\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/category/html\">HTML</a> and CSS that will be responsive, attractive, and user-friendly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to make the form responsive</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have provided the complete code for the registration form in HTML with CSS source code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To make the form responsive to work on mobile and tablet devices you can use media query in CSS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>@media screen and (max-width:767px){\n//your code for mobile here\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Some of the advanced CSS that is used in this form</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using condition for CSS when changing border color and position of the placeholder</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.form label:has(input:focus, input:not(:placeholder-shown)):before {\n                top: -22%;\n                background: #fff;\n                z-index: 1;\n                padding: 0 5px;\n                transform: none;\n                color: #888;\n  }\n .form label:has(input:focus)::before {\n    color: blue;\n }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Changing auto-filled input background color simply background color can\'t be changed but you can use the following trick to override the background by autofill</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.form input:-webkit-autofill {\n  -webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 0 1000px #fff inset !important;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Power of css  ✊</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":457,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/remove-autofill-input-background-html-css.png\" alt=\"registration form in HTML with CSS source code\" class=\"wp-image-457\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So in this article, we have taken you through the process of how to create a registration form and style it with CSS for your website. A well-designed UI for the registration and login form are an essential part of the website which connect user with your website to save to fetch their data on your website so become crucial to keep the registration form easy to understand while user fill out the form.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can further enhance this form according to your requirements like more input validation and error messages and connect it to the backend server or API.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Attractive registration form in HTML with CSS source code', 'Complete source code of Registration form in html with css source code . click on download button to download source code for free', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '422-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-09-14 07:22:20', '2023-09-14 07:22:20', '', 422, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=474', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
