ta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n        <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n        <title>Document</title>\n        <style>\n            /* body{display: flex;align-items: center;min-height: 96vh;} */\n            .form {\n                display: flex;\n                min-height: 400px;\n                width: 700px;\n                border-radius: 8px;\n                box-shadow: 0 0 8px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\n                font-family: sans-serif;\n                overflow: hidden;\n                margin: 10px auto;\n            }\n            .form input,.form select {\n                padding: 10px;\n                color: #555;\n                border: 2px solid #ddd;\n                outline: none;\n                font-size: 16px;\n                width: 100%;\n            }\n           .form input:-webkit-autofill {\n                -webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 0 1000px #fff inset !important;\n            }\n            .form input:focus {\n                border-color: blue;\n            }\n            .form img {\n                width: 50%;\n                min-height: 100%;\n                object-fit: cover;\n            }\n            .form select{margin-bottom: 17px;width: 100%;}\n            .form button {\n                padding: 10px 20px;\n                font-size: 16px;\n                background: blue;\n                color: #fff;\n                border: none;\n                border-radius: 4px;\n                width: 100%;\n            }\n            .form label {\n                position: relative;\n                margin-bottom: 17px;\n            }\n            .form label:has(input:focus, input:not(:placeholder-shown)):before {\n                top: -22%;\n                background: #fff;\n                z-index: 1;\n                padding: 0 5px;\n                transform: none;\n                color: #888;\n            }\n            .form label:has(input:focus)::before {\n                color: blue;\n            }\n            .form input::placeholder {\n                opacity: 0;\n            }\n            .form label::before {\n                color: #ccc;\n                content: attr(for);\n                position: absolute;\n                top: 50%;\n                transform: translateY(-50%);\n                left: 10px;\n                pointer-events: none;\n                transition: all 0.3s;\n            }\n            .form h2 {\n                margin-top: 0;\n            }\n            .form form {\n                padding: 2rem;\n                display: flex;\n                flex-direction: column;\n                justify-content: center;\n            }\n           \n            @media (max-width: 767px) {\n                .form img {\n                    display: none;\n                }\n                .form {\n                    justify-content: center;\n                    width: unset;\n                    align-items: center;\n                }\n            }\n        </style>\n    </head>\n    <body>\n        <div class=\"form\">\n            <img\n                alt=\"register\"\n                src=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/_next/image?url=%2Fdev%2Fabout-frontend.png&w=1080&q=75\"\n            />\n            <form>\n                <h2>Register Now</h2>\n                <label for=\"name\">\n                    <input autofocus placeholder=\"Name\" id=\"name\" type=\"text\" />\n                </label>\n                <select>\n                    <option selected hidden>choose course</option>\n                    <option>BCA</option>\n                    <option>MCA</option>\n                    <option>BTech</option>\n                    <option>BSc</option>\n                </select>\n                <label for=\"email\">\n                    <input autofocus placeholder=\"Email\" id=\"email\" type=\"text\" />\n                </label>\n                <label for=\"password\">\n                    <input placeholder=\"Password\" id=\"password\" type=\"password\" />\n                </label>\n                <label for=\"confirm password\">\n                    <input placeholder=\"confirm password\" id=\"password\" type=\"password\" />\n                </label>\n                \n                   \n                \n                <button>Sign Up</button>\n            </form>\n        </div>\n    </body>\n</html>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<a class=\"theme-btn download-btn\" title=\"registration form in HTML with CSS source code\" id=\"download-registration-html\" href=\"/demo/student-registration-form.html\" download=\"resistration-form-html\">download source code</a>\n<a class=\"theme-btn download-btn ml-md-3\" href=\"/demo/student-registration-form.html\">Preview</a>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to create a Registration form in HTML with CSS source code given above</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To create a registration form you will need html for structure and css for styling form. You will need an HTML and CSS file for HTML structure and styling respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Setting the HTML Structure</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To create html structure create an html file named <strong>registration.html</strong> for example</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;Registration Form&lt;/title&gt;\n    &lt;link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\"&gt; &lt;!-- Include your CSS file here --&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n    &lt;!-- Your registration form content will be here --&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the code above, we are done with the basic structure of an HTML document for form. We have also linked an external CSS file called <strong>style.css</strong>, which we\'ll create shortly to style our registration form.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Create the Registration Form</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, let\'s add the registration form html itself to the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> of the HTML document</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n    &lt;head&gt;\n        &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\" /&gt;\n        &lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" /&gt;\n        &lt;title&gt;Document&lt;/title&gt;\n    &lt;/head&gt;\n    &lt;body&gt;\n        &lt;div class=\"form\"&gt;\n            &lt;img\n                alt=\"register\"\n                src=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fcard.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"\n            /&gt;\n            &lt;form&gt;\n                &lt;h2&gt;Register Now&lt;/h2&gt;\n                &lt;label for=\"email\"&gt;\n                    &lt;input autofocus placeholder=\"Email\" id=\"email\" type=\"text\"/&gt;\n                &lt;/label&gt;\n                &lt;label for=\"password\"&gt;\n                    &lt;input placeholder=\"Password\" id=\"password\" type=\"password\"/&gt;\n                &lt;/label&gt;\n                &lt;label for=\"confirm password\"&gt;\n                    &lt;input placeholder=\"confirm password\" id=\"password\"           type=\"password\" /&gt;\n                &lt;/label&gt;\n                &lt;button&gt;Sign Up&lt;/button&gt;\n            &lt;/form&gt;\n        &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the code above for the HTML form, we have created a registration form which has the following fields:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Email</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>password</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>confirm password</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can add more fields according to your need like first name, last name, mobile number, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Each input element has a unique <code>id</code> and <code>name</code> attribute, which is essential for JavaScript and server-side processing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now add CSS  in style.css and link it to the HTML file</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>style.css\n\n       /* body{display: flex;align-items: center;min-height: 96vh;} */\n            .form {\n                display: flex;\n                height: 400px;\n                width: 700px;\n                border-radius: 8px;\n                box-shadow: 0 0 8px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\n                font-family: sans-serif;\n                overflow: hidden;\n                margin: 10px auto;\n            }\n            .form input {\n                padding: 10px;\n                color: #555;\n                border: 2px solid #ddd;\n                outline: none;\n                font-size: 16px;\n                width: 100%;\n            }\n           .form input:-webkit-autofill {\n                -webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 0 1000px #fff inset !important;\n            }\n            .form input:focus {\n                border-color: blue;\n            }\n            .form img {\n                width: 50%;\n                height: 100%;\n                object-fit: cover;\n            }\n            .form button {\n                padding: 10px 20px;\n                font-size: 16px;\n                background: blue;\n                color: #fff;\n                border: none;\n                border-radius: 4px;\n                width: 100%;\n            }\n            .form label {\n                position: relative;\n                margin-bottom: 17px;\n            }\n            .form label:has(input:focus, input:not(:placeholder-shown)):before {\n                top: -22%;\n                background: #fff;\n                z-index: 1;\n                padding: 0 5px;\n                transform: none;\n                color: #888;\n            }\n            .form label:has(input:focus)::before {\n                color: blue;\n            }\n            .form input::placeholder {\n                opacity: 0;\n            }\n            .form label::before {\n                color: #ccc;\n                content: attr(for);\n                position: absolute;\n                top: 50%;\n                transform: translateY(-50%);\n                left: 10px;\n                pointer-events: none;\n                transition: all 0.3s;\n            }\n            .form h2 {\n                margin-top: 0;\n            }\n            .form form {\n                padding: 2rem;\n                display: flex;\n                flex-direction: column;\n                justify-content: center;\n            }\n            @media (max-width: 767px) {\n                .form img {\n                    display: none;\n                }\n                .form {\n                    justify-content: center;\n                    width: unset;\n                    align-items: center;\n                }\n            }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to use this registration form html &amp; css </h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can use this registration form HTML &amp; CSS either by copying and pasting it into your website or can downloading the file directly and adding it to your website folder. if you are facing any problems in adding this <a href=\"https://codepen.io/tag/registration%20form\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://codepen.io/tag/registration%20form\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">code</a> to your website you can contact me over WhatsApp.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Registration form HTML CSS source code</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now let\'s see how to create a registration form with <a href=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/category/html\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/category/html\">HTML</a> and CSS that will be responsive, attractive, and user-friendly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to make the form responsive</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have provided the complete code for the registration form in HTML with CSS source code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To make the form responsive to work on mobile and tablet devices you can use media query in CSS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>@media screen and (max-width:767px){\n//your code for mobile here\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Some of the advanced CSS that is used in this form</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Using condition for CSS when changing border color and position of the placeholder</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.form label:has(input:focus, input:not(:placeholder-shown)):before {\n                top: -22%;\n                background: #fff;\n                z-index: 1;\n                padding: 0 5px;\n                transform: none;\n                color: #888;\n  }\n .form label:has(input:focus)::before {\n    color: blue;\n }</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Changing auto-filled input background color simply background color can\'t be changed but you can use the following trick to override the background by autofill</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>.form input:-webkit-autofill {\n  -webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 0 1000px #fff inset !important;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Power of css  ✊</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":457,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/remove-autofill-input-background-html-css.png\" alt=\"registration form in HTML with CSS source code\" class=\"wp-image-457\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So in this article, we have taken you through the process of how to create a registration form and style it with CSS for your website. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A well-designed UI for the registration and login form are an essential part of the website which connect user with your website to save to fetch their data on your website become crucial to keep the registration form easy to understand while user fill out the form.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can further enhance this form according to your requirements like more input validation and error messages and connect it to the backend server or API.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Attractive registration form in HTML with CSS source code', 'Complete source code of Registration form in html with css source code . click on download button to download source code for free', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '422-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-09-14 10:53:15', '2023-09-14 10:53:15', '', 422, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=487', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
