(548, 1, '2023-09-16 07:19:09', '2023-09-16 07:19:09', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hi, friends are you wondering for a bog to understand <strong>Armstrong number in JavaScript</strong>? In this article, we will know completely what is Armstrong number and how to get an Armstrong number in javascript.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":530,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/armstrong-number-function-in-javacsript-1024x576.png\" alt=\"what is armstrong number in javascript\" class=\"wp-image-530\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What is Armstrong\'s number in javascript?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An Armstrong number is a number that is equal to the sum of powers of every digit to a number of digits. for example <strong>153</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1^3 + 5^3 + 3^3 = 1 + 125 + 27 = 153</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>number of digits =3 (153) so the power will be 3</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to Check if a Number is an Armstrong Number in javascript</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To check or verify whether a given number is an Armstrong number, you can follow these steps:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Convert the number to a string to count the number of digits.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>define or initialize a variable to keep track of the sum.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Iterate through each digit of the number:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Convert the digit back to an integer if it\'s in string format.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Raise the digit to the power of the number of digits.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Add the result to the sum.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Check if the sum is equal to the original number.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is the way you can check whether a number is an Armstrong number in javascript or any other language using the same logic.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Armstrong number in javascript program</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SO for now we have seen <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=usBN7nUuHNE\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=usBN7nUuHNE\">what is Armstrong\'s number</a> and now we will see the program to check whether a number is Armstrong or not in Javacsript.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Program to check if a number is Armstrong in javascript using for loop</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>function isArmstrongNumber(number) {\n  const numStr = number.toString();\n  const numDigits = numStr.length;\n  let total = 0;\n\n  for (let i = 0; i &lt; numDigits; i++) {\n    total += Math.pow(parseInt(numStr&#91;i]), numDigits);\n  }\n\n  return total === number;\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Program to find Armstrong numbers in the given range of numbers</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>here we will use above defined program to check Armstrong\'s number <strong>isArmstrongNumber</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>function findArmstrongNumbersInRange(start, end) {\n  const armstrongNumbers = &#91;];\n\n  for (let i = start; i &lt;= end; i++) {\n    if (isArmstrongNumber(i)) {\n      armstrongNumbers.push(i);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return armstrongNumbers;\n}\n\n// example \nconst startRange = 1;\nconst endRange = 1000;\nconst armstrongNumbersInRange = findArmstrongNumbersInRange(startRange, endRange);\n\nconsole.log(`Armstrong numbers in the range ${startRange} to ${endRange}:`, armstrongNumbersInRange);</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Without using for loop</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>if you want to check Armstrong\'s number without for loop then you can use the <strong><a href=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/how-to-set-object-key-in-usestate-react-state-hook-with-the-object-and-array\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://www.frontendzone.com/blog/how-to-set-object-key-in-usestate-react-state-hook-with-the-object-and-array\">map </a>function</strong> to loop through and add numbers to get Armstrong\'s number in javascript</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>function isArmstrongNumber(number) {\n  const numStr = number.toString();\n  const numDigits = numStr.length;\n  \n  const sum = numStr\n    .split(\'\')\n    .map(digit =&gt; Math.pow(parseInt(digit), numDigits))\n    .reduce((acc, val) =&gt; acc + val, 0);\n\n  return sum === number;\n}\n\n// Test the function with some examples\nconsole.log(isArmstrongNumber(153));  // Should return true\nconsole.log(isArmstrongNumber(370));  // Should return true\nconsole.log(isArmstrongNumber(371));  // Should return true\nconsole.log(isArmstrongNumber(407));  // Should return true\nconsole.log(isArmstrongNumber(123));  // Should return false\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What is the application of Armstrong Numbers</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We learned about Armstrong numbers in JavaScript and also learned how to verify if a number is an Armstrong number. Now we will know what is real-time use of the Armstrong number is.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Educational Purposes</strong> - The Armstrong number is often used as an educational example to make students userland for loop as for loop is used in the Armstrong program.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Puzzle Games</strong> - Armstrong\'s numbers can be incorporated into puzzle games or brain teasers to create challenging number-based puzzles to find out Armstrong\'s numbers and show the correct answers for multiple problems.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Cryptography</strong> - In some cases, Armstrong numbers can be used in cryptographic algorithms or random number generation, although this is rare and typically not recommended due to their predictable nature.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We\'ve learned what is Armstrong number in javascript, their unique properties, and how to check whether a number is an Armstrong number or not. Additionally, we\'ve written programs in JavaScript code to find Armstrong numbers within a specified range. <strong>This is the most famous question asked in coding interviews for freshers.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '# Best Explanation of the Armstrong number in JavaScript with an Example and 2 programs', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '529-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-09-16 07:19:09', '2023-09-16 07:19:09', '', 529, 'https://cms.frontendzone.com/?p=548', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
