(640, 1, '2023-11-04 10:31:32', '2023-11-04 10:31:32', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s know how to create a popup with html and css only</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Popups can be created with HTML and css only with the help of input and css.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>use the input type checkbox to close and open the popup based on the checked condition of input.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":641,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cms.frontendzone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/popup-htm-css-1024x821.png\" alt=\"popup with html and css only\" class=\"wp-image-641\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>what to use for this</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>1. input type checkbox</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>2. input: checked</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>3. input:not(:checked)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>4. use the label as a button to check or uncheck input</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n  &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n  &lt;meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"&gt;\n  &lt;title&gt;Document&lt;/title&gt;\n  &lt;style&gt;\n    *{\n      box-sizing: border-box;\n      margin: 0;\n      padding: 0;\n      transition: all 0.3s;\n    }\n    body{\n      font-family: sans-serif;\n    }\n    .open{\n      display: inline-block;\n      padding: 10px 20px;\n      background: #000;\n      color: #fff;\n      margin: 40px;\n      border-radius: 10px;\n      cursor: pointer;\n    }\n    .popup{\n      position: fixed;\n      height: 100%;\n      width: 100%;\n      top: 0;\n      